This paper deals with probabilistic top-k queries, which are commonly used in information retrieval and database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new algorithm, which involves computational efficiency, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. The algorithm is based on probability calculations, which can be related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
